No Secchi depth taken- only gauge.  Ice off 3/29- water level was about 3" high at that time.
Best conditions to date.  Calm and sunny.
Ice on lake. 16 degrees F overnight.
Taking over for Fred Kruger.  Ice-off.
Water level low- shorelines exposed.  Very shallow public boat launch site.
Fishing very poor- weeds rapidly emerging all over lake- low water level causing boating hazards (to props etc.) and launching.  Some swimmers itch and rough fish kill.  Suckers.
Low water levels.  Would not swim but boating is okay.  Weeds emerging and blooming- clear- calm- dry- sunny weather.
High weeds- algae increasing- low water level causing hazards to boating.
Rained lightly yesterday- partly cloudy- and lake weeds emerging.
Swimmers itch- weeds- rains raised lake from .67 to .83 in seven days.
Swimmers itch- partly cloudy- fishing poor to bad- and many weeds emerging.
Earlier reading not possible due to high winds all week.
Weeds- clear- sunny- and still getting insect hatches.
Too windy all week for secchi disc readings.
Lake covered with green/brown algae scum.
Clear- sunny- green algae on surface of entire lake- and the air temperature is 74 degrees.
Light chop- bright- sunny- air temperature 40 degrees- weeds browning- and cold weather.
Bright- clear- weeds browning- and no activity on lake.
Dirty brown water entering from commercial cranberry farm.
Duck mites- aircraft spraying chemicals in cranberry farm- stream runs into lake McKenzie-pollution studies unknown.
Floating scum and algae- surface temperature of water is 75 degrees- lots of emerging coontail weeds- especially at river outlet from cranberry farm.
Lots of algae- scum on lake shores- emergent weeds on larger percentage of lake.  Nitrates
Lake has many shallow areas in its center- etc.- therefore- many weedbeds.
Brown sediment near shoreline- floating brown junk- and heavy weeds.
Did not take secchi reading.  Heavy rain month.  Highest lake level of year!
Ice off 4/30/1996- which is later than normal.
Water level constant this year due to much rain.
